WEBVTT

00:01.154 --> 00:10.384
Father, it has been said so clearly already that what needs to happen in this room, a sermon, a human cannot make happen.

00:11.686 --> 00:13.548
Taste and see that the Lord is good.

00:14.309 --> 00:16.191
There is a spiritual taste.

00:16.671 --> 00:29.746
There are capacities for enjoyment in the soul that cannot be awakened any other way than by the miracle of your indwelling, empowering spirit.

00:30.754 --> 00:42.945
So we invite you to come in power and to do that kind of awakening of joy in Jesus that is greater than joy in anything else.

00:44.026 --> 00:45.748
I asked this in his name, amen.

00:47.149 --> 00:50.132
So the focus for the weekend is enjoying Jesus.

00:50.893 --> 01:00.722
And so I want to begin by making the case from the gospel of John that saving faith in Jesus.

01:00.866 --> 01:10.237
So as basic as it can be, saving faith in Jesus is the awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

01:13.261 --> 01:22.532
So I don't think the gospel of John or the New Testament teaches that the enjoyment of Jesus is stage two.

01:23.714 --> 01:30.322
So first you get saved, you believe, and then maybe

01:30.562 --> 01:36.129
Sometimes later you learn that there's such a thing as enjoying Jesus.

01:36.309 --> 01:48.985
I'm arguing that to be saved, to be converted, to be born again, to have saving faith is to experience an awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

01:50.527 --> 01:56.274
And that can be very threatening, very unsettling to you.

01:57.634 --> 02:12.637
because there are genuine believers among you who think that you don't enjoy Jesus and you've been scratching your head since you heard of this church and saw that written right here.

02:12.697 --> 02:14.239
Enjoy Jesus, make disciples.

02:14.840 --> 02:20.970
You've been scratching your head like, is that how essential is that?

02:22.352 --> 02:26.418
And I've just said it's as essential as it can get.

02:27.586 --> 02:34.395
which is scary if you are saying to yourself right now in this room, but I think I'm saved.

02:37.099 --> 02:39.542
And I don't enjoy Jesus.

02:45.069 --> 02:55.623
A few weeks ago, I was in Washington, D.C., sat down at a dinner table, a man sat down beside me who loves our ministry in the sixties.

02:55.663 --> 02:57.586
He had gone through a crisis of it.

02:57.730 --> 03:01.154
two years earlier, and he just confessed to me.

03:01.214 --> 03:13.628
He said, Pastor John, I hope in the Lord, I trust in the Lord, but ever since that crisis, I don't experience joy in Jesus.

03:16.852 --> 03:25.362
And here's a man who's been Christian for 50 years, and he's telling me that he doesn't enjoy Jesus.

03:26.530 --> 03:35.178
And so I responded to him the way I would respond to you if you came up to me after this service and said, I'm a Christian.

03:35.839 --> 03:36.900
I know I'm a Christian.

03:37.501 --> 03:40.724
I trust Jesus, but I don't enjoy Jesus.

03:42.666 --> 03:44.708
I said to him, I don't believe you.

03:48.371 --> 03:54.057
And over the next 15 or 20 minutes, I've said this to many people for 40 years, I've said this to people.

03:54.537 --> 03:55.218
I don't believe you.

03:56.898 --> 04:25.842
For the next 10, 20 minutes we had, we're talking about this very earnestly, I drew out of him significant expressions of glad affections for God, for the goodness of God, for the patience of God, for the power of God, for the preciousness of Christ, affections like thankfulness,

04:27.330 --> 04:33.438
like treasuring Christ, like hope in Christ.

04:34.399 --> 04:43.571
And I pointed out to him, and I'm pointing out to you now, that thankfulness is not a grim emotion.

04:44.713 --> 04:45.694
It's a glad emotion.

04:47.957 --> 04:48.318
It is.

04:48.358 --> 04:54.706
And treasuring Christ is not a gloomy emotion.

04:55.746 --> 05:07.919
It's a glad emotion, even if it exists in the midst of sorrow and there are tears on your face as you are thankful and treasuring Jesus.

05:11.663 --> 05:16.008
Hope is not a dark, cheerless emotion.

05:16.369 --> 05:24.978
It's a glad emotion, even in prison, witness Paul, even in the hospital,

05:25.346 --> 05:26.548
even at the grave side.

05:27.649 --> 05:28.851
Hope is a glad emotion.

05:35.662 --> 05:48.040
In other words, I want to warn you here at the outset that some of you have conceptions of enjoying Jesus that are inadequate.

05:49.282 --> 05:51.826
You have conceptions, ideas in your head,

05:52.770 --> 05:58.617
of what it means to enjoy Jesus that are inadequate to account for biblical reality.

05:59.738 --> 06:04.384
And I'm here to fix him.

06:04.404 --> 06:06.006
Do you have a conception?

06:07.187 --> 06:13.315
Indeed, do you have an experience of joy that can account for 2 Corinthians 6, 10?

06:15.117 --> 06:17.700
Sorrowful, yet always rejoicing.

06:20.223 --> 06:22.546
Sorrowful, yet

06:23.202 --> 06:30.871
Always, not after the sorrow, in, under, through the sorrow, always rejoicing.

06:31.011 --> 06:32.072
You have a category for that.

06:32.372 --> 06:33.694
You have an experience of that.

06:34.234 --> 06:38.559
If you don't, you will not be able to make sense out of this church or the Bible.

06:42.504 --> 06:44.666
Do you have a category that makes sense?

06:44.686 --> 06:51.634
Do you have a conception of enjoying Jesus that makes sense out of 2 Corinthians 7, 4?

06:52.482 --> 06:55.805
where Paul says, in all our afflictions.

06:55.845 --> 07:02.832
Now you gotta pause there and remember chapter 11, chapter six, where he lists 26 horrors that he walks through.

07:03.213 --> 07:15.365
Paul lived a life of continual threat and sorrow and grief and pain in and out of prison, in and out of beatings, in and out of lacerations on his back, in and out of conflicts.

07:15.645 --> 07:20.210
He lived a life of continual weeping, I would dare say.

07:22.146 --> 07:27.272
And he says, in all our afflictions we are overflowing with joy.

07:27.332 --> 07:35.202
And you just want to say, Paul, do you have a conception of joy that can account for that?

07:36.403 --> 07:40.088
Do you have an experience of joy that would make sense out of that?

07:40.348 --> 07:47.377
Or Ecclesiastes, I told the staff today, I was going to quote Ecclesiastes for the first time in defense of Christian hedonons.

07:47.397 --> 07:47.857
So here it is.

07:50.320 --> 07:51.762
Ecclesiastes 7, 3.

07:52.322 --> 08:03.318
Sorrow is better than laughter because by sadness of faith, the heart is made glad.

08:03.378 --> 08:11.529
You just want to shake your head and say, what possibly could that be?

08:13.372 --> 08:17.778
By sorrow of faith, tears stained face.

08:21.666 --> 08:24.430
The heart is made glad.

08:25.751 --> 08:27.333
Here's my paraphrase.

08:29.957 --> 08:44.055
There are experiences of loss and grief in life that take you to depths of joy you could not have known any other way.

08:44.836 --> 08:46.898
If you're old enough, you know what I'm talking about.

08:47.679 --> 08:49.842
Brand new Christians, maybe not.

08:50.178 --> 08:54.848
If you've walked with the Lord long enough, you know what he's talking about.

08:55.149 --> 09:08.338
There are dark nights, there are losses, there are griefs, there are struggles, there are sorrows where he shows up and he's tasted in that, in a way, he could not be tasted any other way.

09:10.274 --> 09:13.237
So I'm asking you, do you have categories in your head?

09:13.257 --> 09:20.925
Do you have conceptions and ideas about what the enjoyment of Jesus is so that you don't jump to the conclusion?

09:21.186 --> 09:24.009
I guess I'm not a Christian because I don't.

09:25.410 --> 09:26.071
Are you sure?

09:26.111 --> 09:31.817
So let me work on this with you in John, John's gospel for a bit.

09:32.418 --> 09:40.146
And I'm hoping that by the time we're done, the only people that think you're an unbeliever in this room would be unbelievers.

09:41.282 --> 09:42.604
And we really care about you.

09:43.024 --> 09:44.285
This church cares about you.

09:44.926 --> 09:45.927
And I care about you.

09:46.068 --> 09:47.029
And we're praying.

09:47.069 --> 09:54.958
We've prayed weeks before and in the room earlier today that you would know him and enjoy him before we're done.

09:56.880 --> 09:58.502
So all that by way of warning.

09:59.223 --> 10:09.074
I'm just warning you not to be too pessimistic about yourself as I lay out the argument that saving face

10:10.018 --> 10:13.603
is the awakening of the enjoyment of Jesus.

10:17.129 --> 10:39.762
One of the most provocative statements about saving faith is that the book in the Bible that talks most about coming to eternal life through saving faith, namely the Gospel of John,

10:41.346 --> 10:54.959
never uses the word faith in all 21 chapters and uses the word believe 98 times.

10:54.979 --> 11:00.464
The noun belief or faith does not occur in the Gospel of John.

11:01.866 --> 11:05.929
The verb believe occurs 98 times.

11:09.153 --> 11:10.674
That cannot be an accident.

11:13.282 --> 11:18.730
And I've spent a lot of time thinking, I want to understand, John, why you did it that way.

11:19.651 --> 11:21.674
What were you thinking?

11:23.036 --> 11:32.008
That must have taken some effort to use the word pistillo 98 times and never use the word pistis faith.

11:35.092 --> 11:39.639
So this message is an effort to explain why that is.

11:40.921 --> 11:42.002
And I make no

11:42.754 --> 11:55.690
The pretense that I've got the whole thing figured out, because the Gospel of John, probably more than any other book in the Bible, has layers of meaning.

11:57.131 --> 12:05.522
It is a mysteriously layered book, which is why you give it to brand new believers.

12:09.927 --> 12:12.530
And it's the deepest book there is, maybe.

12:13.698 --> 12:16.041
At least that's my experience of the Gospel of John.

12:16.081 --> 12:18.204
You take off, oh, I get that.

12:19.045 --> 12:23.550
For God's the love of the world, he gave his only son, whoever believes in him, and not perish, and have eternal life.

12:23.810 --> 12:24.591
Give that everywhere.

12:24.852 --> 12:27.174
Hang it over, ball-filled fences.

12:29.698 --> 12:39.610
And then you get this massive doctrine of predestination in chapter 10, and the election, and then he's...

12:39.630 --> 12:39.890
Okay.

12:40.034 --> 12:41.576
So that's the mystery for me.

12:41.596 --> 12:47.424
98 times the verb, zero times the noun, what's he up to?

12:49.467 --> 13:01.464
Sometimes scholars, pastors will say, okay, what he's up to is that he's trying to show that faith is active.

13:03.807 --> 13:05.169
And that sounds right.

13:06.490 --> 13:09.074
Faith is active, but

13:10.114 --> 13:28.092
When you stay with that explanation a few minutes, what they usually mean is faith produces action, meaning if you believe in Jesus, you become a loving person, which is true.

13:29.293 --> 13:30.354
It bears fruit.

13:31.815 --> 13:33.657
Now, that's true.

13:34.178 --> 13:38.802
I don't think that's what John is up to.

13:39.330 --> 13:44.315
John would say, faith is action.

13:44.375 --> 13:47.458
It doesn't just bring about action.

13:50.401 --> 13:52.142
That's where I'm starting.

13:54.084 --> 13:55.406
I'm going to check that out.

13:56.186 --> 13:59.349
Can you show that in the gospel?

13:59.430 --> 14:08.178
That faith in itself, before it produces anything, is a soul or a heart action.

14:09.890 --> 14:16.117
That's what I think is going on when he uses the verb 98 times and the noun never.

14:17.178 --> 14:21.703
The acting of the soul, the acting of the heart before there's any fruit.

14:22.765 --> 14:23.666
It clearly is fruit.

14:23.746 --> 14:25.488
Love is the fruit of faith.

14:27.149 --> 14:34.738
Now keep in mind before I show you some text to that effect, keep in mind we are talking about saving faith.

14:36.162 --> 14:43.253
Whoever believes in the sun, believes verb, whoever believes in the sun has eternal life.

14:43.794 --> 14:50.424
He says that 336, 315, 316, 524, 640, 647, 1125, 2031.

14:51.005 --> 14:55.852
I mean, this book is about believing so that you have eternal life.

14:55.872 --> 14:57.074
It's a saving faith.

14:57.282 --> 15:00.285
If you don't believe, you don't have eternal life, you perish.

15:00.706 --> 15:01.787
This is a big deal.

15:02.067 --> 15:03.229
It's as big as it gets.

15:03.629 --> 15:10.156
We're not talking about a kind of faith that's kind of later, maybe you pray and you're having a faith to heal somebody or something like that, a gift of faith.

15:10.316 --> 15:11.518
We're not talking about that.

15:12.459 --> 15:21.509
We're talking about the most basic experience of salvation, namely, faith that brings eternal life.

15:21.829 --> 15:22.650
What is it?

15:23.151 --> 15:24.352
What's the nature of it?

15:25.293 --> 15:26.194
What's it like?

15:26.690 --> 15:31.218
I'm just asking what, because most of you in this room are believers.

15:32.560 --> 15:38.169
And you should know, in fact, you spend your life coming to know, what did God do to me?

15:39.611 --> 15:40.733
What's going on in me?

15:41.895 --> 15:43.257
This is a divine miracle.

15:43.598 --> 15:44.079
What is it?

15:44.620 --> 15:45.782
How do I experience it?

15:47.244 --> 15:50.349
So to answer that question, what is the acting of faith?

15:51.090 --> 15:53.234
Let's go first to John chapter one.

15:54.370 --> 15:57.774
verses 11 to 13, very familiar text.

15:57.794 --> 16:04.243
Even if you don't look it up, you're sure welcome to look it up and follow with me, but if you don't, you'll recognize it, probably.

16:05.945 --> 16:07.046
Jesus came to His own.

16:07.086 --> 16:09.610
This is John 1, verse 11.

16:10.010 --> 16:14.456
Jesus came to His own, and His own people did not receive Him.

16:16.098 --> 16:22.226
But to all who did receive Him, who believed in His name, now notice the

16:23.426 --> 16:26.429
You can call that a positive in grammar.

16:28.331 --> 16:32.775
To all who did receive him, comma, who believed in his name.

16:34.096 --> 16:37.460
So believing, receiving, interpret each other.

16:38.401 --> 16:46.689
He gave the right to become children of God who were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.

16:47.910 --> 16:51.954
So John chooses to report this language

16:52.738 --> 16:59.526
To make plain, receiving Jesus is what believing does.

17:01.408 --> 17:03.350
So if you say, what's the action of believing?

17:03.690 --> 17:08.836
What does believing do before it produces any action outside with the body?

17:09.777 --> 17:10.478
What does it do?

17:10.698 --> 17:13.441
And the answer is it receives Jesus.

17:14.462 --> 17:16.605
That's what it says in verse 12 there.

17:16.985 --> 17:21.490
But to all who did receive him, comma, who believed in his name,

17:22.498 --> 17:23.860
So believing is receiving.

17:24.160 --> 17:30.307
And don't, even though it's right to apply this to conversion, don't restrict it to conversion.

17:33.690 --> 17:37.975
We could sing right now, Jesus, I do now receive him.

17:38.316 --> 17:42.000
More than all in him I find, he has granted me forgiveness.

17:42.560 --> 17:43.842
I am his and he is my.

17:43.862 --> 17:47.085
I think you can believe her on a sing that all day long every day.

17:47.426 --> 17:50.309
Every hour, Jesus, I do now receive you.

17:50.649 --> 17:51.250
I hope.

17:52.162 --> 17:55.527
that right now, as I'm speaking, I am receiving Jesus.

17:56.388 --> 18:04.621
As my mind is freed up not to think about you, but to think about this text, I'm thinking, Jesus, come, come.

18:06.123 --> 18:06.964
I need more of you.

18:07.144 --> 18:10.189
I'm utterly, totally reliant upon you.

18:10.209 --> 18:13.734
We heard from Jimmy, he up, holds the universe by the word and his power.

18:14.215 --> 18:18.081
I have my existence, my being through the present working of Jesus Christ.

18:18.201 --> 18:19.983
I need you right now.

18:20.003 --> 18:21.746
I do receive you.

18:22.146 --> 18:24.288
You're not getting saved all over again.

18:24.308 --> 18:30.876
You just experience the ongoing coming in presence of Jesus Christ in your life.

18:31.256 --> 18:38.544
So when I say believing is receiving Him, I don't mean just at the beginning, I mean for the rest of your days.

18:39.125 --> 18:42.709
On into eternity, we will be receiving Jesus.

18:42.749 --> 18:48.815
We will be utterly, totally dependent on the moment by moment work of Jesus coming into our lives to sustain us.

18:49.916 --> 18:51.378
Now, double question.

18:51.842 --> 18:56.809
in response to that statement, believing is receiving of Jesus.

18:58.071 --> 18:59.473
Receiving as what?

19:02.678 --> 19:05.603
You receive Him as what?

19:06.103 --> 19:07.586
That's the next question.

19:10.250 --> 19:16.459
And what is the heart doing in the receiving of Jesus?

19:17.260 --> 19:21.266
What's the actual experience of receiving Jesus as

19:21.826 --> 19:22.947
black.

19:22.967 --> 19:25.310
So let's try to answer those from the Gospel of John.

19:25.830 --> 19:32.658
So I'm gonna give two answers, and I'm gonna take you to some texts that support these answers.

19:32.998 --> 19:33.899
First answer.

19:34.900 --> 19:43.610
Receiving Jesus is the soul's drinking of the living water that Jesus is.

19:45.612 --> 19:51.378
Drinking with sweet soul satisfaction, or to use the language of this church,

19:53.154 --> 19:54.635
drinking with enjoyment.

19:57.679 --> 20:09.170
Receiving Jesus is the drinking of the living water that He is to the soul's satisfaction in Him or the enjoyment of Him.

20:09.190 --> 20:10.091
That's answer number one.

20:10.151 --> 20:10.932
Answer number two.

20:12.293 --> 20:21.042
Receiving Jesus is the soul's soul's eating the bread of heaven, which He is.

20:22.402 --> 20:29.874
to the soul's satisfaction of its hunger or the enjoyment of Jesus.

20:29.954 --> 20:35.443
So those are two ways in the Gospel of John to answer the question, what is it to receive Jesus?

20:35.723 --> 20:36.584
Receive as what?

20:36.745 --> 20:38.087
Receive as living water?

20:38.327 --> 20:40.150
Receive as bread from heaven?

20:42.393 --> 20:47.682
So that receiving becomes drinking and receiving becomes eating.

20:48.743 --> 20:50.386
The soul can eat.

20:50.786 --> 20:54.790
the soul can drink and be satisfied.

20:55.891 --> 20:57.292
So now we're at the key verse.

20:57.532 --> 21:00.195
If you want to look at it, this is chapter six verse 35.

21:05.560 --> 21:15.650
This verse has been powerfully effective in my life, transformative in the way I think about faith.

21:18.032 --> 21:20.114
So John six verse 35,

21:20.738 --> 21:25.724
shows that Jesus is the eternally satisfying bread.

21:26.045 --> 21:28.528
He's the eternally satisfying water.

21:28.868 --> 21:33.874
Now if you just stop and think about bread and water, this is not the Lord's Supper.

21:34.015 --> 21:35.256
Just put that aside.

21:35.496 --> 21:36.798
Don't get mixed up with that.

21:36.818 --> 21:39.101
This is water, not wine, and not fruit of the vine.

21:39.121 --> 21:40.503
This is water and bread.

21:41.203 --> 21:43.366
Water and bread are fluid and nourishment.

21:43.586 --> 21:46.450
You just die if you don't have either of them, right?

21:46.722 --> 21:48.344
If you don't have fluid, you die.

21:48.384 --> 21:49.926
If you don't have nourishment, you die.

21:50.346 --> 21:51.868
That's true of eternal life.

21:54.992 --> 22:00.378
But you just have to ask, okay, to have eternal life, you've got to have the right fluid and the right nourishment.

22:00.418 --> 22:00.899
And what is it?

22:01.059 --> 22:01.660
It's Jesus.

22:02.801 --> 22:03.903
That's what he's saying.

22:03.923 --> 22:08.188
So let's read chapter 6, verse 35.

22:08.348 --> 22:11.872
I am the bread of life.

22:13.033 --> 22:13.554
There it is.

22:15.202 --> 22:20.890
Whoever comes to me shall not hunger.

22:22.212 --> 22:28.462
And whoever believes in me shall never thirst."

22:30.284 --> 22:33.289
Wow.

22:33.309 --> 22:39.738
Now notice the parallel between coming and believing, right?

22:39.758 --> 22:42.162
Whoever comes to me shall not hunger.

22:42.498 --> 22:46.444
And then he repeats it, only he replaces the word come with believe.

22:46.864 --> 22:50.049
Whoever believes in me shall never thirst.

22:51.050 --> 22:55.677
So I draw from that parallel, what is believing?

22:55.717 --> 22:57.059
What's the action of believing?

22:57.139 --> 23:02.326
Believing is a coming to Jesus to drink to the soul's satisfaction.

23:02.346 --> 23:07.173
Coming to Jesus is to eat the bread of life to the soul's satisfaction.

23:07.193 --> 23:08.115
That's what believing is.

23:08.455 --> 23:10.578
They run parallel here.

23:12.834 --> 23:20.163
There's no spatial, geographic, physical movement in faith.

23:22.186 --> 23:23.327
But I say there's an action.

23:25.329 --> 23:26.471
It's not like this.

23:27.352 --> 23:29.094
My hand is moving from here to here.

23:29.515 --> 23:32.518
There's no physical movement in faith.

23:32.799 --> 23:34.521
Faith is the movement of the soul.

23:34.581 --> 23:38.706
The soul is in the spatial reality.

23:41.218 --> 23:42.780
It's the movement of hunger.

23:43.982 --> 23:45.384
It's the movement of thirst.

23:47.166 --> 23:48.588
That's the categories you have to have.

23:48.748 --> 23:54.296
When you think about the soul moving, coming to Jesus, coming to Jesus, well, Jesus, where is he?

23:54.336 --> 23:54.816
Where is he?

23:54.836 --> 23:57.981
If he were here, I could walk over here and embrace him.

23:58.962 --> 24:00.044
He's not here like that.

24:00.825 --> 24:02.387
He's here spiritually.

24:03.348 --> 24:04.249
His spirit is here.

24:04.510 --> 24:10.738
To come to Jesus is an action of the soul, and the soul doesn't move geographically.

24:11.554 --> 24:12.856
How does it move?

24:12.916 --> 24:13.797
How does it come?

24:13.857 --> 24:16.720
It comes with hunger.

24:19.644 --> 24:20.885
It comes with thirst.

24:22.507 --> 24:25.731
Coming to water is the movement of thirst.

24:25.831 --> 24:29.075
Coming to bread is the movement of hunger.

24:29.536 --> 24:32.099
These are soul movements, not body movements.

24:32.920 --> 24:41.330
They are heart actions, desiring, longing, drinking, feeding, embracing,

24:41.442 --> 24:43.084
tasting, feasting.

24:43.444 --> 24:53.676
I mean, I'm sure if you come to this church long enough, there will be a great vocabulary developed of enjoying Jesus.

24:54.377 --> 24:55.218
Lots of words.

24:56.219 --> 24:57.661
That was a bunch of them right there.

24:59.503 --> 25:09.394
Words by which the soul feeds on the bread of heaven and the soul drinks the water of life.

25:11.138 --> 25:22.353
Now notice an implication in John 635 about eternity and never-ending satisfaction.

25:23.795 --> 25:29.783
Shall not hunger, you see that in the first part, shall never thirst.

25:30.183 --> 25:36.291
Whoever comes to me shall not hunger, whoever believes in me shall never thirst.

25:37.393 --> 25:38.514
So the words not

